@page "/discipline/section6"
@layout Gsystem.Layout.SimpleLayout
<PageTitle>Section 6: Appeal Process</PageTitle>

<div class="discipline-content">
    <div class="content-header">
        <h1>Section 6: Appeal Process</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">DepEd School Discipline Rules of Procedure</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-body">
        <div class="section-card">
            <h2>6.1 Right to Appeal</h2>
            <p>Students and their parents/guardians have the right to appeal disciplinary decisions:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Appealable Decisions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Suspensions of more than 3 days</li>
                    <li>Expulsion recommendations</li>
                    <li>Transfer to alternative programs</li>
                    <li>Any decision affecting student's educational record</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Non-Appealable Decisions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Verbal warnings</li>
                    <li>Written warnings</li>
                    <li>Short-term detentions (1-3 days)</li>
                    <li>Minor disciplinary measures</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>6.2 Appeal Timeline</h2>
            <p>Appeals must be filed within the specified timeframes:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Filing Deadlines</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Initial Appeal:</strong> Within 5 school days of decision</li>
                    <li><strong>District Level:</strong> Within 10 school days of school decision</li>
                    <li><strong>Division Level:</strong> Within 15 school days of district decision</li>
                    <li><strong>Regional Level:</strong> Within 20 school days of division decision</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Emergency Appeals</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>For expulsion cases: 24-hour expedited process</li>
                    <li>For safety-related issues: Immediate review</li>
                    <li>For special circumstances: Flexible timeline</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>6.3 Appeal Procedures</h2>
            <p>The appeal process follows a structured format:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Step 1: Written Appeal</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Submit written appeal to school principal</li>
                    <li>Include specific grounds for appeal</li>
                    <li>Provide supporting evidence</li>
                    <li>Request specific relief or remedy</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Step 2: School Level Review</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Principal reviews original decision</li>
                    <li>Considers new evidence or information</li>
                    <li>May modify, uphold, or reverse decision</li>
                    <li>Provides written response within 5 days</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>6.4 Higher Level Appeals</h2>
            <p>If unsatisfied with school-level decision, appeals may proceed to:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>District Level Appeal</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Submit appeal to District Supervisor</li>
                    <li>Include all previous documentation</li>
                    <li>Request hearing if desired</li>
                    <li>Receive decision within 10 days</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Division Level Appeal</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Submit appeal to Division Superintendent</li>
                    <li>Include all previous documentation</li>
                    <li>May request formal hearing</li>
                    <li>Receive decision within 15 days</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Regional Level Appeal</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Submit appeal to Regional Director</li>
                    <li>Final administrative level</li>
                    <li>Formal hearing may be required</li>
                    <li>Receive decision within 20 days</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>6.5 Appeal Hearing Process</h2>
            <p>For formal appeals, a hearing may be conducted:</p>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Hearing Preparation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Notify all parties of hearing date</li>
                    <li>Provide access to all relevant documents</li>
                    <li>Arrange for appropriate accommodations</li>
                    <li>Ensure impartial hearing officer</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Hearing Procedures</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Opening statements from all parties</li>
                    <li>Presentation of evidence and witnesses</li>
                    <li>Cross-examination of witnesses</li>
                    <li>Closing statements</li>
                    <li>Hearing officer deliberation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>6.6 Appeal Decision Criteria</h2>
            <p>Appeal decisions shall be based on:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Legal Standards</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Compliance with due process requirements</li>
                    <li>Appropriateness of disciplinary measures</li>
                    <li>Consistency with school policies</li>
                    <li>Protection of student rights</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Factual Considerations</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Accuracy of incident reports</li>
                    <li>Reliability of witness testimony</li>
                    <li>Relevance of evidence presented</li>
                    <li>Student's individual circumstances</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>6.7 Appeal Outcomes</h2>
            <p>Appeal decisions may result in:</p>
            
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Possible Outcomes</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Uphold:</strong> Original decision stands</li>
                    <li><strong>Modify:</strong> Reduce or change disciplinary measures</li>
                    <li><strong>Reverse:</strong> Overturn original decision</li>
                    <li><strong>Remand:</strong> Return to school for reconsideration</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Implementation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Appeal decisions are final and binding</li>
                    <li>Must be implemented immediately</li>
                    <li>Student record updated accordingly</li>
                    <li>All parties notified of final decision</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>6.8 Special Considerations</h2>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>Students with Disabilities</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Additional procedural safeguards</li>
                    <li>Special education coordinator involvement</li>
                    <li>Manifestation determination review</li>
                    <li>Appropriate alternative placements</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
                <h3>Legal Representation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Right to legal counsel at all levels</li>
                    <li>Parent/guardian may represent student</li>
                    <li>Advocate or support person allowed</li>
                    <li>Translation services if needed</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

